<br>
It is early in the day and I take my mages to ME to whack a few Gorangas.  I usually set up at the tree just south of DSP zone in and pull to there.<br>
<br>
A wizard shows up and sees 4 Gorangas standing there and got so excited he started rounding them up to quad kite.  Well he was in such a hurry that he forgot to mem his AoE snare.  <br>
<br>
The wizard zones.  No big deal, just a few mobs out of their normal pathing.<br>
<br>
Wizard zones back in and starts up again.  Mind you, this is early in the morning so there are maybe 5 people in the zone, 3 of them me.<br>
<br>
He gets his 4 Gorangas and promptly has 2 Goranga adds, one of them a Hunter.  He then picks up a mind worm and pulls the whole thing BEHIND me.  Well, as you can imagine, when he runs back past me towards the zone, the whole mess jumps my guys.<br>
<br>
I ran all 3 toons to zone and barely made it out.  I was very lucky.<br>
<br>
The wizard apologizes while my guys and one other are recovering in DSP.  I asked nicely that he not bring his trains/kites close to my camp as it took me 20 minutes to get the pets I wanted. (Not lvl, not an issue any longer.  I was using 52 fire and recast until I got chain stun version.)<br>
<br>
Ok, we all get back in and get set up again.  Wizard picks up his first group and immediately gets a tribesman add.  He pulls the whole thing past me while I am out getting my first mob.  He zones while I am trying to get the stuff off me.  So, he has zoned and now his whole mess is pisssed at me.  I am down to quarter health.<br>
<br>
Now, imagine trying to go through the mobs standing at zone-line with only a quarter health.  So I head straight for the middle of the zone and CoH Dreald with Zreald.  Dreald makes it back to camp with 147 HP's.<br>
<br>
I sent a tell to wizard explaining what happens when he runs his train over someone then zones.<br>
<br>
He apologized and said he was through for the night and would log in his cleric to rez the dead.  Which he did.<br>
<br>
He then came over and buffed all 3 of my toons and 3 pets to the teeth!<br>
<br>
Go figure.  But I still would have been much further ahead if he just wouldn't have been there.  Because now, there we were all buffed up with no one to train us.......<br>
<br>
*rant off*<br>
